tle> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character creation</span><hr size=1> I am faced with the same problem. I am a twinkaholic any how and in 3 years have never been able to stick with just one character for more then a month at a time. I have created and deleted 5 characters already, I just can't seem to make up my mind what to do. By nature, I should be something neutral because I kinda tend to follow my own path, neither good, nor evil. I thought about a druid, but I have been one of those. I am also considering a pet class since I have never played one beyond level 8, I just tend to have a really hard time keeping interest in the casters. A SK would probably be best for me, but then I would be evil <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>HRLP!! I do like to be helpful and group a lot...so has anyone been able to notice a shortage or over abundance of any classes yet? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulikewhatever.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Like whatever</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/11/01 10:02:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Character creation</span><hr size=1> I always create characters with a personal agenda that may or may not risk anyone's life along the way to further said agenda.  Such as drow, and their scheming but I do this with every personality.  The end goal usually determines the race I play or vice versa.  My brother had a problem with deciding what character he wanted to play, so after many successive characters he finally just moved to PvP to try and become lord of Blackburrow.  If you can't decide or just LIKE being low level, then there is a large place in the PvP servers (namely rallos where there are level limits but you can kill anyone).  At level 12 if you can successfully fund armor and weapons beyond your level a ranger is great PvP, snare and bowshot and you can kite most PCs.  Another way to determine a character is to try to plot out your RL personality and adjust it to the world of Norrath.  Are you a scientific analytical person?  If so would you care more for physical science or ethereal science (magic?), etc.  Try to constantly narrow down your choices until you find a race/class you like.  You don't necessarily have to just close your eyes and pick by chance.  I hope not many dwarves are so mathematically gifted as Nife suggests, I mean they have an INT of 60 or so while I've seen stupider high elves with an INT of 92, but there are exceptions to every rule.  I would think gnomes shout off percentages and degrees while dwarves drink and say &quot;no dangit, move here and swing like DAT!  YAH now you got it!&quot; instead of 3.7degrees here and there :P.<br><br>Although you can RP to alter these preconceptions, when someone else looks at your character's race they USUALLY get these impressions.<br><br>Dark elf = Evil, Intelligent, Malicious<br>Ogre = Stupid, Brutal, Beastial (and evil, tho I happen to think they are just stupid and have too much adrenaline.  and also being manipulated by the dark elves)<br>Troll = nearly same as Ogre, though nastier and perhaps quicker<br>Human = lots of preconceptions, but these are the base IMHO...Average, Unpredictable, clumsy?, honorable?<br>High Elf = Superiority complex, graceful, beautiful, angelic<br>Wood Elf = Natural, Agile (cat-like), quick, &amp; in most cases &quot;ally&quot; (unless u play evil character)<br>Erudite = not angelic or as graceful as high elves, but roughly the same. add EXTREMELY powerful if you are playing a character with any intelligence you would figure that out seeing just one.<br>Half -Elf = too many preconceptions to guage, but share physical ideals with wood elves more than humans since everyone notices the pointed ears.<br>Dwarf = Mighty, fearsome, bad breath ( :P ), wise<br>Gnome = Uh I run when I see gnomes, especially if they have some new mech toy, but small, weak, very ODD, and very intelligent.  (everyone knows they love toys too, and knows of their dangers and/or usefullness)<br>Halfling = trickster, quick, curious, strong when they must but resort to tricks rather than strength more often<br>iksar = tons of preconceptions oddly enough, but malicious is not an accurate enough way to describe their anger.  big ego thing, deep culture, and rebellious attitude.<br><br>These are truly my preconceptions, but when you create a character most people will have similar ideas when they see your character.  If you want to advertise one of these then you might want to think of which race best does so (in your opinion).  Shortage of classes? I cant find enough warriors really, or paladins and SKs really but more often them.  it's more the combo than the actual race or class itself.  a DE war ain't popular as barb war, human druid ain't as popular as wood elf or halfling, etc.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usaryiadarkshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saryia Darkshadow</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.erols.com/daniel.mileaf/spot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/11/01 4:02:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left cl